│ THOUGHT: My previous patch was incorrect because it only handled subloops, but the issue occurs within a single loop where control flow creates different contexts. The miscompilation   │
│ happens because `ScalarEvolution` incorrectly assumes that a condition on an induction variable (`%indvar3 != 0`) in the current iteration implies a property (`%indvar2 > 0`) for a PHI │
│ node (`%indvar2`) that holds the induction variable's value from the *previous* iteration.                                                                                               │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ This off-by-one error in reasoning happens when `ScalarEvolution` tries to determine the range of `%indvar2` under the assumption that `%indvar3 != 0`. The core of this reasoning is in │
│ `ScalarEvolution::getRange`. When `getRange` is called on a `SCEVUnknown` that wraps a PHI node, it can try to use assumptions about other values in the current scope to refine the     │
│ range. This is where the mistake happens.                                                                                                                                                │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ To fix this, I need to make `getRange` more conservative. Specifically, when `getRange` is asked for the range of a `SCEVUnknown` that corresponds to a PHI node, it should not try to   │
│ refine this range using contextual assumptions from the same loop. It should just return the full range for the type. This prevents it from making incorrect deductions based on the     │
│ state of other variables in the current iteration.                                                                                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ I will modify `ScalarEvolution::getRange` in `llvm/lib/Analysis/ScalarEvolution.cpp`. I'll add a check at the beginning of the function. If the input `SCEV` is a `SCEVUnknown` wrapping │
│ a `PHINode`, the function will immediately return the full range for the PHI's type, effectively disabling the faulty range refinement for this case.                                    │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -i '/ConstantRange ScalarEvolution::getRange(const SCEV \*S) {/a \                                                                                                                   │
│   if (auto *SU = dyn_cast<SCEVUnknown>(S))\                                                                                                                                              │
│     if (isa<PHINode>(SU->getValue()))\                                                                                                                                                   │
│       return ConstantRange(SU->getType()->getIntegerBitWidth(), /*isFullSet=*/true);\                                                                                                    │
│ ' llvm/lib/Analysis/ScalarEvolution.cpp                                                                                                                                                  │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
