│ Given the repeated failures and the complexity of `ScalarEvolution`, a more direct and robust approach is needed. Instead of trying to fix the intricate logic within `ScalarEvolution`, │
│ I will prevent the `indvars` pass from performing this specific, incorrect optimization.                                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The optimization happens when `IndVarSimplify` tries to simplify the users of an induction variable. The function `simplifyUsersOfIV` (which is not a member of a class, but a static    │
│ function in `IndVarSimplify.cpp`) iterates over the users of an IV and tries to simplify them. For `icmp` instructions, it calls `simplifyICmpInst`. This is where the incorrect folding │
│ to `true` occurs.                                                                                                                                                                        │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ To fix this, I will modify `IndVarSimplify.cpp` to disable this simplification for the specific pattern that causes the bug. The problematic pattern involves an `icmp` whose operand is │
│ a PHI node (`%indvar2`) that is itself dependent on another induction variable (`%indvar3`).                                                                                             │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ I will add a check at the beginning of `simplifyICmpInst` in `IndVarSimplify.cpp`. If either operand of the `ICmpInst` is a PHI node that belongs to a loop header, I will immediately   │
│ return, skipping any attempt to simplify the instruction. This is a conservative but safe fix that directly prevents the miscompilation without risking breaking other valid             │
│ optimizations in `ScalarEvolution`.                                                                                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
